Harbin, a riverside city that depends on Songhua River for water sourcing, has been forced to shut down its water supply system for four days starting from wee hours on Wednesday because a highly polluted water stretch in the Songhua River, which was caused following a blast with a petrochemical plant near one of the river's main tributary early this month, has been passing through the city.
